a) Keyboard and Mouse Activities
i) Mouse Activities (Click, Double Click, Hover)
 Click Activity

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio → Create/Open workflow
Step 2: Drag Click activity into the Sequence
Step 3: Click Indicate on screen
Step 4: Select the button or element on the screen
Step 5: Go to Properties Panel
Step 6: Set ClickType = CLICK_SINGLE
Step 7: Run the workflow

Double Click Activity

Step 1: Drag Double Click activity
Step 2: Click Indicate on screen
Step 3: Select the target (e.g., desktop icon)
Step 4: Run the workflow

Hover Activity

Step 1: Drag Hover activity
Step 2: Click Indicate on screen
Step 3: Select the element
Step 4: Run the workflow

ii) Type Into Activity

Step 1: Drag Type Into activity
Step 2: Click Indicate on screen
Step 3: Select a text field (e.g., search bar)
Step 4: In the Text field, enter:

"Hello UiPath"

Step 5: (Optional) Click + (Plus icon) to add special keys like Enter
Step 6: Run the workflow

iii) Type Secure Text Activity

Step 1: Create a SecureString variable (e.g., password)
Step 2: Drag Type Secure Text activity
Step 3: Click Indicate on screen and select password field
Step 4: In SecureText property, enter the variable
Step 5: Run the workflow

 b) Triggering Events
i) Element Triggering Event

Step 1: Drag Monitor Events activity
Step 2: Inside it, drag On Element Appear
Step 3: Click Indicate on screen
Step 4: Select a pop-up or button
Step 5: In Event Handler, drag Message Box
Step 6: Enter message text
Step 7: Run the workflow

ii) Image Triggering Event

Step 1: Drag Monitor Events activity
Step 2: Inside it, drag On Image Appear
Step 3: Click Indicate on screen
Step 4: Select/draw area around image or logo
Step 5: In Event Handler, add action (e.g., Message Box)
Step 6: Run the workflow

iii) System Triggering Event

Step 1: Drag Monitor Events activity
Step 2: Inside it, drag System Trigger
Step 3: Go to Properties Panel
Step 4: Set Type (e.g., Low Battery / Power Connected)
Step 5: Add action in Event Handler
Step 6: Run the workflow

c) Launch Assistant Bot using Keyboard Event (Hotkey)

Step 1: Create a New Sequence (name it: HotKeyTrigger)
Step 2: Drag Monitor Events activity

Step 3: Inside Triggers section, drag Hotkey Trigger

Step 4: Go to Properties Panel

Set Key = S
Enable Alt / Ctrl checkbox

Step 5: Inside Event Handler, drag activities (e.g., open website, show message)

Step 6: Run the workflow

Step 7: Press Alt + S (or your selected key)

Result: Bot executes the assigned task
